213	\begin{corollary}\leanok
214	[Cotangent space at a section]
215	  \label{cor:cotangent_at_section}
216	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.cotangent_at_section}
217	  \uses{thm:smooth_iff_locally_free_omega}
218	  If $f \colon X \to S$ is smooth of relative dimension $n$ and $s \colon S \to X$ is a section of $f$, then the cotangent space $s^*\Omega_{X/S}$ is a locally free $\struct{S}$-module of rank $n$. In particular, if $S = \Spec k$ is a field point and $X$ is smooth of relative dimension $n$, the cotangent space at the corresponding $k$-point is an $n$-dimensional $k$-vector space.
219	\end{corollary}
220	
221	\begin{proof}
222	  \uses{thm:smooth_iff_locally_free_omega, def:relative_kaehler_sheaf}
223	  \leanok
224	  The cotangent space along $s$ is by definition the pullback $s^*\Omega_{X/S}$, i.e.\ the image of $\Omega_{X/S}$ under the pullback functor $s^* = \texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,s$. By Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_iff_locally_free_omega}, the smoothness hypothesis on $f$ implies that $\Omega_{X/S}$ is locally free of rank $n$ as an $\struct{X}$-module. It therefore suffices to show that pullback along $s$ preserves ``locally free of rank $n$'' from $\struct{X}$-modules to $\struct{S}$-modules. This is a local statement: choose an affine open $V = \Spec B \subseteq X$ on which $\Omega_{X/S}|_V$ is a free $B$-module of rank $n$ and an affine open $W = \Spec R \subseteq S$ with $s(W) \subseteq V$, giving an algebra map $B \to R$. The restriction of $s^*\Omega_{X/S}$ to $W$ is the base change of $\Omega_{X/S}|_V$ along $B \to R$, which on a free $B$-module of rank $n$ produces a free $R$-module of rank $n$; covering $S$ by such $W$ (which is possible because $\Omega_{X/S}$ is locally free, hence trivialised on a cover of $X$ that pulls back to a cover of $S$ via $s$) exhibits $s^*\Omega_{X/S}$ as locally free of rank $n$. The relevant Mathlib infrastructure is \texttt{SheafOfModules.pullbackObjFreeIso} (in \texttt{Mathlib.Algebra.Category.ModuleCat.Sheaf.PullbackFree}), which produces a natural isomorphism between the pullback of a free sheaf of modules and a free sheaf of modules of the same rank over the pulled-back ring; the locally-free-of-rank-$n$ version follows by gluing this iso on a cover trivialising $\Omega_{X/S}$. This is the content of Hartshorne~II, Corollary~8.10.
225	
226	  The specialisation to a $k$-point of a smooth $k$-scheme is the case $S = \Spec k$ in the above: a section $s \colon \Spec k \to X$ is exactly a $k$-rational point, and a locally-free $\struct{\Spec k}$-module of rank $n$ is a $k$-vector space of dimension $n$. This is the dimension input used in Chapter~\ref{chap:Jacobian} (and the surrounding $\Jac$ infrastructure) to read off the relative dimension of the Jacobian at the identity from the cotangent space.
227	\end{proof}
