229	\section{Curves and the canonical sheaf}
230	
231	The case of a smooth proper curve $C \to \Spec k$ is the special case $n = 1$: the relative cotangent sheaf $\Omega_{C/k}$ is a line bundle on $C$, classically denoted $\omega_C$ and called the \emph{canonical sheaf}.
